### Description
<!-- âœï¸--> A clear and concise description of the problem or missing capability...
We have some resolvers and guards that we would like to run on every navigation between children and some that should run only when navigating to a children, but not when navigating between the children. Currently we can only configure the behaviuour with runGuardsAndResolvers on a global level. It would really help to be able to configure this per guard/resolver.

### Describe the solution you'd like

resolver:
```
{
  path: 'detail/:id',
  component: HeroDetailComponent,
  resolve: {
    hero: {
      class: HeroResolver,
      run: 'always', // probably same options as for the global runGuardsAndResolvers setting
    }
  }
}
```

guards:
```
{
  path: 'admin',
  loadChildren: () => import('./admin/admin.module').then(mod => mod.AdminModule),
  canLoad: [
    {
      class: AuthGuard,
      run: 'always', // probably same options as for the global runGuardsAndResolvers setting
    }
  ]
}
```

### Describe alternatives you've considered

Not using guards/resolvers... but then other stuff like scrollPositionRestoration wont work.

